Part B
: Knowing that $a \approx 9.8$ m/s^2 , and specifying $r = 4050mi$ (that is, 100 mi above the surface of the Earth), we solved for $v$: $$v = \sqrt{a \times r} = \sqrt{9.8 \text{m}\, \text{s}^{-2} \times 4050 \text{mi}} = 191.5 \sqrt{\text{m}\cdot\text{mi}\strut}\ \text{s}^{-1}$$

